WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:08.486
- Previously on "Happy!"...

00:08.530 --> 00:10.227
- [screaming]
[explosion]

00:10.271 --> 00:11.881
- You want us to catch
the son of a gun, don't you?

00:11.924 --> 00:14.188
- He said--
- Who said?

00:14.231 --> 00:15.841
- The bunny.

00:15.885 --> 00:17.452
- I'm Scooter frickin'
Sterling.

00:17.495 --> 00:19.062
My safe word is Tallahassee.

00:19.106 --> 00:20.890
[muffled screaming]

00:20.933 --> 00:22.544
[switch clicks]

00:22.587 --> 00:25.068
- Everybody loves revenge,
right? Even you.

00:25.112 --> 00:28.637
- I don't have a vengeful bone
in my body.

00:28.680 --> 00:31.553
- There's something living
in your mind, Blue.

00:31.596 --> 00:33.424
[distant screaming]
- [pounds on glass]

00:33.468 --> 00:36.210
- Orcus, God of Death.

00:36.253 --> 00:40.127
With Isabella dead,
you will have no escape.

00:40.170 --> 00:42.129
[yelling]

00:42.172 --> 00:44.174
You will never be free.

00:44.218 --> 00:45.697
- Dad got me
kicked out of school.

00:45.741 --> 00:48.396
- Maybe this is exactly
what she needs.

00:48.439 --> 00:51.094
You've noticed this place
runs 40,000 a year?

00:51.138 --> 00:53.531
- I'll give you 1,000 bucks
if you find me a girl.

00:53.575 --> 00:55.620
- Aah!

00:55.664 --> 00:58.232
- Is that a liver?

00:58.275 --> 00:59.276
What's something like
that worth?

00:59.320 --> 01:00.799
- Over 100,000.

01:00.843 --> 01:02.627
- Holy giblets,
I'm standing in the middle

01:02.671 --> 01:04.803
of a goddamn gold mine
of blood and guts.

01:05.935 --> 01:08.894
[dramatic music]

01:08.938 --> 01:15.118
♪

01:27.304 --> 01:29.915
[organ thuds]

01:29.959 --> 01:31.613
♪

01:31.656 --> 01:32.918
[organ thuds]

01:32.962 --> 01:40.187
♪

01:44.016 --> 01:47.455
[snapping]
[grunting]

01:47.498 --> 01:49.892
[buzzer sounds]
- Ouch!

01:51.763 --> 01:53.722
- [echoing] Hailey,
what are you doing here?

01:53.765 --> 01:56.942
- [echoing] That really hurt.

01:56.986 --> 02:00.555
It says, "Take out the kidney
for $100,000."

02:02.861 --> 02:04.820
- I don't even know--
What the f--

02:04.863 --> 02:06.387
What the f--

02:06.430 --> 02:09.433
[lights clicking]

02:11.043 --> 02:13.176
- Go on, Dad. Do it.

02:13.220 --> 02:14.873
Go on, Dad. Do it.
- Uh..

02:14.917 --> 02:17.224
- Go on, Dad. Do it.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.834
Please don't touch
the sides again.

02:18.877 --> 02:20.009
- Uh...

02:20.052 --> 02:21.358
- And don't touch the sides.

02:21.402 --> 02:23.447
- Okay.

02:30.933 --> 02:33.327
[electricity buzzing]

02:33.370 --> 02:34.806
- I'm scared.
- No need to be scared.

02:34.850 --> 02:36.504
I got this.

02:36.547 --> 02:38.897
- [echoing] You don't
look like you got this.

02:38.941 --> 02:41.422
- Quiet, or I'll--

02:41.465 --> 02:42.901
Be quiet.

02:42.945 --> 02:46.601
[tongs squeal,
electricity buzzing]

02:46.644 --> 02:48.255
- Be careful.

02:48.298 --> 02:50.344
- You got some serious issues,
my man.

02:50.387 --> 02:52.694
[electricity buzzing]

02:52.737 --> 02:55.392
[creaking]

02:55.436 --> 02:56.698
[buzzer sounds]
- [screaming]

02:56.741 --> 02:59.396
- [gasps]
- Professor Wondercakes?

02:59.440 --> 03:00.876
[doorbell buzzes]

03:00.919 --> 03:02.791
- [grumbling]

03:02.834 --> 03:05.489
- Hailey!

03:05.533 --> 03:06.838
- You okay?

03:06.882 --> 03:09.406
- No, I got to pee.

03:09.450 --> 03:12.801
- I was running late.
Didn't have time for breakfast.

03:12.844 --> 03:14.411
- Huh?
[door closes]

03:14.455 --> 03:16.457
- You're taking her today,
remember?

03:16.500 --> 03:17.893
- Like it was yesterday.

03:17.936 --> 03:19.764
- It was yesterday.
- It was yesterday.

03:19.808 --> 03:22.332
- ♪ I'm M.C. Happy,
and I'm here to say ♪

03:22.376 --> 03:24.726
♪ Hey, hey, hey,
we got Hailey all day ♪

03:24.769 --> 03:26.510
[imitates record scratching]

03:26.554 --> 03:28.382
- Um...

03:28.425 --> 03:30.035
maybe you should get a sitter.

03:30.079 --> 03:31.733
- Sitters aren't free, Nick.
- I know.

03:31.776 --> 03:34.301
- Besides,
she'd rather be with you.

03:34.344 --> 03:38.261
And I think some quality time
together wouldn't hurt.

03:38.305 --> 03:39.436
- She'd rather be with me?

03:39.480 --> 03:41.699
- You can do this, Nick.
- I can?

03:41.743 --> 03:43.527
- Just feed her...
- Check!

03:43.571 --> 03:45.486
- Keep her out of trouble...
- Abso-tively!

03:45.529 --> 03:47.618
- Help with her essay.
- Posi-lutely!

03:47.662 --> 03:48.880
- Wait, what?
- For St. Melanie--

03:48.924 --> 03:50.404
something to help them
get to know her.

03:50.447 --> 03:52.928
- Nobody knows her
better than me!

03:52.971 --> 03:54.408
- It's due tomorrow.
- Wait a minute.

03:54.451 --> 03:55.757
Hold--hold on a second.

03:55.800 --> 03:56.845
What are we,
Communists all of a sudden?

03:56.888 --> 03:58.412
She's not even in school,

03:58.455 --> 03:59.804
they're giving her
homework assignments?

03:59.848 --> 04:01.893
- Nick, please.
- I know, it's just...

04:01.937 --> 04:03.634
[inhales deeply]

04:03.678 --> 04:06.463
[whispering] We've never
been together for a whole day.

04:06.507 --> 04:08.117
- You're going to do great.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.771
She's crazy about you.

04:09.814 --> 04:10.946
- Aww.

04:10.989 --> 04:13.340
- Just remember the rules.

04:15.385 --> 04:16.647
- Oh, the rules. Yeah.

04:16.691 --> 04:18.127
- Don't sweat it, buddy.
Happy's here--

04:18.170 --> 04:20.434
the bestest bestie
in the whole wide world.

04:20.477 --> 04:22.827
And if anyone knows
what Hailey likes, it's me!

04:22.871 --> 04:24.046
- Yeah.

04:24.089 --> 04:25.830
- Got anything in the fridge?

04:25.874 --> 04:27.092
- Yeah, go ahead.
Knock yourself--

04:27.136 --> 04:28.093
[grunts]

04:28.137 --> 04:31.314
[refrigerator whirring]

04:33.534 --> 04:34.491
Uh...

04:34.535 --> 04:35.927
[bell dings]

04:35.971 --> 04:38.103
[whimsical music]

04:38.147 --> 04:42.151
- Follow me! Follow me!

04:42.194 --> 04:44.632
♪ To a world
of make-believe ♪

04:44.675 --> 04:46.982
♪ Where silly bears
have crazy hair ♪

04:47.025 --> 04:49.419
♪ Wear shorts and dungarees

04:49.463 --> 04:51.508
♪ If the stuffings are frayed
or the bow's too tight ♪

04:51.552 --> 04:53.118
♪ Don't you pout,
we'll make it right ♪

04:53.162 --> 04:56.513
♪ At the huggery-buggery

04:56.557 --> 04:59.647
♪ Hoogery-sugary

04:59.690 --> 05:03.694
♪ World of make-believe

05:03.738 --> 05:06.436
Can you feel the magic?

05:06.480 --> 05:09.004
[children laughing]

05:09.047 --> 05:12.703
Oh, man, look at all
these fun little numbers.

05:14.226 --> 05:17.578
- Oh, what you got there?
A cop bear.

05:19.841 --> 05:21.799
- Where you ever in A.A.?

05:21.843 --> 05:24.802
[upbeat music playing faintly]

05:24.846 --> 05:27.152
♪

05:27.196 --> 05:29.372
- I haven't had
an avocado in years.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.505
[rim shot]

05:31.548 --> 05:33.071
- Seriously, Dad.

05:33.115 --> 05:35.813
♪

05:35.857 --> 05:38.555
- All right, okay, uh...

05:38.599 --> 05:41.036
Let's be real
with each other today.

05:41.079 --> 05:42.777
Um...

05:42.820 --> 05:46.520
I used to enjoy an
adult beverage back in the day,

05:46.563 --> 05:51.089
and now
I never touch the stuff.

05:51.133 --> 05:54.702
♪

05:54.745 --> 05:57.182
Could you fix mine?

05:57.226 --> 05:59.054
It looks like a spree killer.

05:59.097 --> 06:00.577
- Sure.

06:00.621 --> 06:02.231
- [sighs]

06:02.274 --> 06:04.189
[spraying]

06:06.104 --> 06:08.150
[sniffs]

06:08.193 --> 06:09.586
How's the essay coming?

06:09.630 --> 06:11.545
- I don't really know
what to write.

06:11.588 --> 06:12.894
♪

06:12.937 --> 06:14.548
- They just want
to know more about you.

06:14.591 --> 06:17.768
You know, um...
the kind of stuff you like.

06:17.812 --> 06:19.596
♪

06:19.640 --> 06:22.991
- I don't know.
- Ooh, I know!

06:23.034 --> 06:25.123
♪

06:25.167 --> 06:26.603
- What would you write?

06:26.647 --> 06:29.084
- Me? I, uh...

06:29.127 --> 06:33.523
Well, I mean, um...

06:33.567 --> 06:35.177
Um...

06:35.220 --> 06:36.918
♪

06:36.961 --> 06:40.791
Self-reflection was never
really my strong suit.

06:40.835 --> 06:44.621
- Did you like being a cop?

06:44.665 --> 06:45.622
- Aah!

06:45.666 --> 06:48.625
[aggressive music]

06:48.669 --> 06:50.105
♪

06:50.148 --> 06:52.803
- Nick!
- Too much paperwork.

06:57.286 --> 06:59.680
You know this bear situation--
- Sucks.

06:59.723 --> 07:01.116
- Right?
- Pretty much.

07:01.159 --> 07:02.291
- Oh, praise the Lord.

07:02.334 --> 07:04.162
You want to blow
this clambake?

07:04.206 --> 07:06.774
- Really?
- [chuckling] Yeah.

07:06.817 --> 07:10.038
- "Easter Under Siege,"

07:10.081 --> 07:13.084
"Bunny Bombing Causes
Market Surge,"

07:13.128 --> 07:15.609
and my personal favorite,

07:15.652 --> 07:19.874
"Here Comes Evil Cottontail."

07:19.917 --> 07:21.702
Got to love the "Post."

07:23.747 --> 07:25.183
We're a hit, baby!

07:25.227 --> 07:26.924
[laughing]

07:26.968 --> 07:31.233
Oh, people need Sonny Shine's
Easter now more than ever.

07:31.276 --> 07:34.062
The inspiration came to me last
Christmas, did you know what?

07:34.105 --> 07:35.846
- You might've
mentioned it, yes.

07:35.890 --> 07:39.023
- "Sicko Santa Claus
snatches tiny tights

07:39.067 --> 07:41.156
for pervo purposes."

07:41.199 --> 07:43.811
The bleeding headlines.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.508
Now, you think it would be
a big black eye

07:45.552 --> 07:46.640
for the holiday, right?

07:46.683 --> 07:47.989
But you know what happened?

07:48.032 --> 07:49.904
both:
Sales went through the roof.

07:49.947 --> 07:54.299
Holly-jolly bonanza! It was
the biggest Christmas ever.

07:54.343 --> 07:56.606
Why?

07:56.650 --> 08:00.262
Because people are
sick puppies, that's why.

08:00.305 --> 08:05.223
Sex sells,
death sells even better.

08:05.267 --> 08:07.269
I wish I had a witness.

08:07.312 --> 08:09.532
Someone who could
really appreciate me

08:09.576 --> 08:11.142
for the visionary that I am!

08:11.186 --> 08:15.233
Someone who could just see me
eye to eye!

08:15.277 --> 08:17.801
[ominous music]

08:17.845 --> 08:19.586
- Something wrong?

08:19.629 --> 08:23.198
- You know when you try not
to look at something, but...

08:23.241 --> 08:27.028
it just makes
you look at it more?

08:27.071 --> 08:29.378
- No.

08:29.421 --> 08:31.772
[Western music]

08:31.815 --> 08:34.035
- Wyoming.

08:34.078 --> 08:38.213
♪

08:38.256 --> 08:41.042
- I-I don't see you
in the tumbleweeds, my friend,

08:41.085 --> 08:44.262
with the cow pies and such?

08:44.306 --> 08:48.615
- You think this
is a goddamn joke, Geno?

08:48.658 --> 08:50.268
♪

08:50.312 --> 08:52.314
- No, absolutely not.

08:52.357 --> 08:54.969
- Good, because...

08:55.012 --> 08:57.754
Wyoming...

08:57.798 --> 08:59.756
is where I plan to be.

08:59.800 --> 09:01.279
♪

09:01.323 --> 09:06.023
Leave all of this crime
and punishment behind and...

09:06.067 --> 09:07.895
start over.

09:07.938 --> 09:09.636
♪

09:09.679 --> 09:11.638
Regular American life.

09:11.681 --> 09:14.118
♪

09:14.162 --> 09:15.946
Norman Rockwell.

09:15.990 --> 09:17.731
♪

09:17.774 --> 09:19.733
Spring is in the air, Geno.

09:19.776 --> 09:22.605
Even in this hole,
I can smell it,

09:22.649 --> 09:27.610
and I am gonna take a deal
with the Feds.

09:27.654 --> 09:29.960
♪

09:30.004 --> 09:31.614
- Blue...

09:31.658 --> 09:34.312
you cannot do that.

09:34.356 --> 09:36.097
Y-you know how this works.

09:36.140 --> 09:38.055
You got to do your time,
you got to be a stand-up guy.

09:38.099 --> 09:39.753
- Stand-up--
[seethes]

09:39.796 --> 09:42.059
You--

09:42.103 --> 09:43.800
You're my fucking lawyer.

09:43.844 --> 09:45.802
- Yeah, but I'm
your friend first,

09:45.846 --> 09:47.238
and I don't want to see you

09:47.282 --> 09:49.066
finally get out of this place
in a bag.

09:49.110 --> 09:51.286
- Don't you see? That's exactly
why I got to get out of here.

09:51.329 --> 09:52.896
I got to take the deal.

09:52.940 --> 09:55.333
Knowing what I know,
do you really think...

09:55.377 --> 09:57.031
[door closes in the distance]

09:57.074 --> 10:01.339
You-know-who
is gonna let me live?

10:01.383 --> 10:03.994
- Y-you're emotional right now.
- Hmm.

10:04.038 --> 10:05.692
- It's understandable,

10:05.735 --> 10:08.738
but, Blue,
as long as you keep quiet,

10:08.782 --> 10:11.132
you are safer here
than in Wyoming

10:11.175 --> 10:14.091
or Tahiti
or Timbuk-big-titty-tu.

10:14.135 --> 10:17.094
[ominous music]

10:17.138 --> 10:20.097
- [chuckles wryly]

10:20.141 --> 10:22.752
You're not my friend.

10:22.796 --> 10:26.669
You are not my friend.
You are my barrister.

10:26.713 --> 10:31.108
Call the goddamn Feds,
take the goddamn deal,

10:31.152 --> 10:34.285
and, motherfucker...

10:34.329 --> 10:38.855
I had better be wearing
a plaid shirt by Easter.

10:38.899 --> 10:42.859
♪

10:42.903 --> 10:45.862
[solemn music]

10:45.906 --> 10:52.434
♪

10:52.477 --> 10:55.437
[upbeat music playing,
children shouting happily]

10:55.480 --> 11:00.050
♪

11:00.094 --> 11:02.400
[indistinct chatter]

11:02.444 --> 11:05.186
[ominous music]

11:05.229 --> 11:08.189
[whirring]

11:08.232 --> 11:14.238
♪

11:19.504 --> 11:21.289
- Pray tell?

11:21.332 --> 11:24.988
[whirring]

11:25.032 --> 11:31.125
♪

11:31.168 --> 11:34.345
- [groans]

11:34.389 --> 11:36.304
Kill me.

11:37.914 --> 11:40.090
- [groans]

11:40.134 --> 11:43.311
The breath--
[clears throat]

11:43.354 --> 11:46.923
Only a true friend
would tell you. Yeah.

11:46.967 --> 11:49.752
- [gagging]
- Open up. Open.

11:49.796 --> 11:52.886
- [gagging]

11:52.929 --> 11:54.931
- There we go.

11:54.975 --> 11:57.891
Now, you listen to me,

11:57.934 --> 12:02.112
I have removed all of the skin
from your body.

12:02.156 --> 12:04.462
It is not
a survivable condition.

12:04.506 --> 12:06.073
Fatal infection is inevitable

12:06.116 --> 12:07.901
if your heart
doesn't shut down first.

12:07.944 --> 12:12.209
So, you see,
I already have killed you.

12:12.253 --> 12:15.952
- Oh.
Well, okay, then,

12:15.996 --> 12:19.434
- The question is,
"How long?"

12:19.477 --> 12:23.220
- Uh-huh.
- The answer is...

12:23.264 --> 12:25.832
precisely as long
as I require.

12:25.875 --> 12:27.921
♪

12:27.964 --> 12:29.792
You see...

12:29.836 --> 12:33.100
I am not some...

12:33.143 --> 12:35.058
grinning idiot clown

12:35.102 --> 12:38.453
who's putting on a show
for the YouTube crowd.

12:38.496 --> 12:41.935
I am a master craftsman.

12:41.978 --> 12:45.503
I will determine
your time of death

12:45.547 --> 12:48.245
down to the hour...

12:48.289 --> 12:52.467
[whispering]
The minute, the second.

12:52.510 --> 12:54.817
So, until then,

12:54.861 --> 12:57.602
and until precisely then...

12:57.646 --> 12:59.213
- [groans, panting]

12:59.256 --> 13:01.519
- Hang in there, baby.

13:03.913 --> 13:06.002
- Stupid, stupid, stupid.

13:06.046 --> 13:07.787
I knew she didn't play
with toys anymore.

13:07.830 --> 13:09.266
How could I be such a dummy?

13:09.310 --> 13:11.660
I got to regroup,
get my head in the game.

13:11.703 --> 13:13.401
God knows
the Harlem Globetrotters

13:13.444 --> 13:15.490
did not become the best
baseball team in the world

13:15.533 --> 13:17.797
by dwelling
on every single loss!

13:19.537 --> 13:21.757
- Why don't you,
um, write about cancer?

13:21.801 --> 13:23.585
You know, everybody loves
a good tearjerker.

13:23.628 --> 13:25.369
- It's supposed to be about me.

13:25.413 --> 13:29.634
- And, you know,
just be yourself.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.811
I mean, you know,
no one likes a phony.

13:31.854 --> 13:33.290
[glass squeaks]

13:33.334 --> 13:35.771
- All right, Salaam.

13:35.815 --> 13:37.817
- Ah...

13:41.821 --> 13:44.301
[sighs]
- Where are we going?

13:44.345 --> 13:45.694
- I haven't a clue,

13:45.737 --> 13:49.350
but, uh, I'm gonna put on
my thinking cap.

13:49.393 --> 13:53.615
♪

13:53.658 --> 13:55.617
I'm gonna put on
my thinking cap.

13:55.660 --> 13:58.446
- Oh, right.
Thinking cap mode activated!

13:58.489 --> 14:00.622
Uh, things Hailey likes.

14:00.665 --> 14:03.668
Tickle fights, patty-cake,
tutus, baby dolls,

14:03.712 --> 14:04.931
ponies, magic tricks--

14:04.974 --> 14:06.019
- Wait a minute,
that's it.

14:06.062 --> 14:07.977
- What's it?

14:08.021 --> 14:09.849
- Kid, how do you feel
about ponies?

14:09.892 --> 14:12.025
[swing music]

14:12.068 --> 14:15.593
- She had to be 15,
maybe 16 lengths back...

14:15.637 --> 14:18.466
- Welcome to OTB.

14:18.509 --> 14:19.510
- Wow.

14:19.554 --> 14:21.077
[bell ringing]

14:21.121 --> 14:24.646
- Off-track betting,
where the ponies run all day.

14:24.689 --> 14:27.083
[men shouting]

14:28.606 --> 14:31.392
Breath like an ashtray,
grip like a python.

14:31.435 --> 14:34.395
- Hey, Saxy.
- Lena! Well, well, well.

14:34.438 --> 14:36.745
This is my kid...
Hailey.

14:36.788 --> 14:40.140
- Oh. Ain't you a sweet dish?

14:40.183 --> 14:41.924
- So you're
my dad's girlfriend?

14:41.968 --> 14:44.361
- For about 32 seconds.

14:44.405 --> 14:46.842
- You promised--
no gambling.

14:46.886 --> 14:48.626
You already broke
one promise, Nick.

14:48.670 --> 14:50.802
Well--well, several,
actually.

14:50.846 --> 14:52.413
Pretty much all of them.

14:52.456 --> 14:54.110
If you do it again,
we're in big trouble.

14:54.154 --> 14:56.765
- We're not gambling.
We're watching people gamble.

14:56.808 --> 14:59.159
Will you relax--
Will you look at her?

14:59.202 --> 15:01.901
It's like Bambi frolicking
in the fresh fallen snow.

15:01.944 --> 15:03.728
I mean, the kid loves it.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.556
I mean,
it's no Club Teddy Bear.

15:05.600 --> 15:07.689
I grant you that.
- That's a low blow.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.778
- Ha!
Like punching blueberries.

15:09.821 --> 15:12.041
Hey, yo, scumbag.
Scram.

15:12.085 --> 15:13.521
[bugle playing]

15:13.564 --> 15:15.044
Oh, you got
a racing form, huh?

15:15.088 --> 15:16.741
- Ponies have weird names.

15:16.785 --> 15:19.483
- Well, they're weird animals.

15:19.527 --> 15:21.833
I, uh, once knew a pony named
Social Disease.

15:21.877 --> 15:24.706
She ran so good,
I got weak in my...

15:24.749 --> 15:26.055
right eye.

15:26.099 --> 15:28.188
Um, all right,
let's do a tutorial here.

15:28.231 --> 15:30.930
Uh, see these numbers here?
Those are the odds.

15:30.973 --> 15:34.585
So you get a horse like, uh,
this glistening specimen,

15:34.629 --> 15:36.936
Tijuana Trots,
who pays 20 to 1.

15:36.979 --> 15:38.676
That's a 20-to-1 dog
in my book.

15:38.720 --> 15:41.027
- She not a dog.
She's a horsey.

15:41.070 --> 15:43.855
- So, anyway, you place
a bet on Tijuana Trots,

15:43.899 --> 15:45.988
she comes in first place,
that pays out--

15:46.032 --> 15:47.598
- $42.

15:47.642 --> 15:48.730
- How'd you know that?

15:48.773 --> 15:50.732
- Math, Dad.
What about this one?

15:50.775 --> 15:52.908
- Uh, okay,
Mom's Molasses,

15:52.952 --> 15:55.563
that's a name that doesn't
inspire confidence.

15:55.606 --> 15:59.915
- She's 9 to 2,
that's 11 bucks on a $2 bet.

15:59.959 --> 16:01.743
both: Not too shabby.

16:01.786 --> 16:05.529
- Says here she placed
in her last two races on--

16:05.573 --> 16:07.836
What's D mean?
- Dirt.

16:07.879 --> 16:10.230
So you want to go
with Mom's Molasses?

16:10.273 --> 16:11.971
Well, we're not gonna bet
any real cash.

16:12.014 --> 16:13.450
- Okay.

16:13.494 --> 16:15.061
But do you know
what I say we do?

16:15.104 --> 16:19.500
How about if we just bet
100-large imaginary?

16:19.543 --> 16:21.154
- Let's do it.

16:21.197 --> 16:24.984
- Now, where on earth might
I find some imaginary cash?

16:25.027 --> 16:27.812
♪

16:27.856 --> 16:29.771
[bell ringing]
- And they're off!

16:29.814 --> 16:31.120
Mom's Molasses falls
way behind.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.253
I've never seen a horse
so slow.

16:33.296 --> 16:35.211
- Mom's Molasses--
you sure are.

16:35.255 --> 16:37.605
Okay, well, that's what you get

16:37.648 --> 16:39.259
for letting big dumb animals
take your money.

16:39.302 --> 16:41.565
I know this is hard
to believe, but...

16:41.609 --> 16:43.480
- Mom's Molasses and Pretender
in Chief are neck in neck!

16:43.524 --> 16:45.787
- I've never been, um, lucky
when it comes to the ponies.

16:45.830 --> 16:47.528
You know,
maybe you're exactly--

16:47.571 --> 16:50.139
- It's Mom's Molasses!
- Yes! Yes!

16:50.183 --> 16:51.967
- Holy cheese nuts!

16:52.011 --> 16:53.577
We would've won, like,
five grand!

16:53.621 --> 16:54.839
- $550.

16:54.883 --> 16:57.146
- All right, smarty pants,
who's up next?

16:57.190 --> 16:58.843
- I want Mr. Plinkett.

16:58.887 --> 17:01.237
Says here she placed
in her last three races.

17:01.281 --> 17:03.631
- Same jockey on her back,
she just went up a class.

17:03.674 --> 17:05.067
- Easy.
She's a 50-to-1 shot.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.590
I mean, that horse
has been ridden harder than--

17:06.634 --> 17:09.028
- Don't you dare!
- 100 imaginary.

17:09.071 --> 17:10.507
Let's do this.

17:10.551 --> 17:11.769
- You heard the lady.

17:11.813 --> 17:15.512
- This don't grow on trees,
you know.

17:15.556 --> 17:17.123
You see what's happening?

17:17.166 --> 17:19.908
You're seducing Hailey into
a dark, depraved world

17:19.951 --> 17:21.910
of cheap laughs
and easy cash!

17:21.953 --> 17:23.259
- [whispering]
Just relax.

17:23.303 --> 17:26.741
Just let her have this
while it lasts, huh?

17:26.784 --> 17:28.525
Do you know what
the Sax family crest is?

17:28.569 --> 17:30.266
Two iguanas
licking the tears of despair

17:30.310 --> 17:32.225
out of each other's eyes
because they lost it all

17:32.268 --> 17:33.226
on a sure thing.

17:33.269 --> 17:35.228
- Mr. Plinkett wins!

17:35.271 --> 17:36.838
- Until today!

17:36.881 --> 17:39.188
My baby is a gold mine!

17:39.232 --> 17:40.581
[both cheering]

17:40.624 --> 17:41.886
You're a natural!

17:41.930 --> 17:43.888
What do you say we do this
with money?

17:43.932 --> 17:45.586
- Really?
- Real money!

17:45.629 --> 17:47.588
[both laugh]

17:47.631 --> 17:50.025
♪

17:50.069 --> 17:51.548
Did you have any?

17:51.592 --> 17:53.550
- Yeah, I have 40 bucks.

17:53.594 --> 17:55.639
- Good, all right.

17:55.683 --> 17:57.119
Get to work.
- Okay.

17:57.163 --> 18:00.905
- I wish I had better news.
He wants to make a deal.

18:00.949 --> 18:02.559
- Like Monty Hall?

18:02.603 --> 18:04.213
- No, like, with the Feds.

18:04.257 --> 18:05.693
I tried to talk him out of it--

18:05.736 --> 18:06.998
[blender whirs]

18:07.042 --> 18:08.696
I-I tried to talk
him out of it--

18:08.739 --> 18:10.263
[blender whirs]
The dumb son of a bitch wants--

18:10.306 --> 18:12.134
[blender whirs]

18:12.178 --> 18:13.918
Witness protection--
[blender whirs]

18:13.962 --> 18:15.964
Witness protection--
[blender whirs]

18:16.007 --> 18:19.968
Something about--
[blender whirring]

18:25.147 --> 18:26.888
[whirring stops]
Something about Wyoming!

18:26.931 --> 18:28.237
[rattling]

18:28.281 --> 18:30.021
- Didn't he get the bug?

18:30.065 --> 18:31.936
- Between you and me,
Mr. Shine,

18:31.980 --> 18:33.895
the man is a few peas short
of a casserole.

18:33.938 --> 18:35.375
I-I've seen it happen
a thousand times.

18:35.418 --> 18:38.160
Guys can't take the pressure,
they just crack.

18:38.204 --> 18:39.901
- Pressure?

18:39.944 --> 18:41.598
[sighs]

18:41.642 --> 18:42.643
[lid pops]

18:42.686 --> 18:44.688
Pressure.

18:44.732 --> 18:46.995
Three square meals a day.

18:48.257 --> 18:51.260
Ample time for exercise
and hobbies.

18:54.220 --> 18:57.223
A cozy cot in every room.

18:57.266 --> 18:59.660
Plenty of chums...

18:59.703 --> 19:03.142
with a similar backgrounds
and interests.

19:03.185 --> 19:07.058
Pressure is what I do.

19:09.148 --> 19:13.021
Pressure is remaking
the world's oldest holiday

19:13.064 --> 19:15.066
from the ground up.

19:16.764 --> 19:18.766
And I do it alone.

19:25.076 --> 19:28.167
[sighs] Let's go ahead
and kill the idiot.

19:29.907 --> 19:31.909
[slurping]

19:33.215 --> 19:35.304
[indistinct chatter]
- I mean, Jesus.

19:35.348 --> 19:37.263
I can't believe your mom
gave you 40 bills.

19:37.306 --> 19:38.786
- Mom thinks you're broke.

19:38.829 --> 19:40.266
- Wonder where she got
that idea.

19:40.309 --> 19:42.659
- Well, not for long!
You know what I'm feeling?

19:42.703 --> 19:44.792
The early-bird special
at Red Lobster.

19:44.835 --> 19:46.794
How about you?
- Hell, yeah.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.143
- Language!

19:48.187 --> 19:49.753
- Ah, you got to watch
your language.

19:49.797 --> 19:50.972
- Can't let her do this, Nick.
- And, you know,

19:51.015 --> 19:52.843
this little bet
that we're gonna do,

19:52.887 --> 19:54.976
um, it's a one-time thing,
all right?

19:55.019 --> 19:56.195
- It's Mom.
- Don't answer that.

19:56.238 --> 19:58.153
- Hi, Mom!
- Finally.

19:58.197 --> 19:59.328
You're in for it now, Nick.

19:59.372 --> 20:00.938
If I can't knock any sense
into you,

20:00.982 --> 20:02.157
maybe Amanda can.

20:02.201 --> 20:04.290
- What happened to fun?

20:04.333 --> 20:05.813
[tapping]

20:05.856 --> 20:06.814
"Are you ready?
Here comes the fun."

20:06.857 --> 20:08.250
Remember that?

20:08.294 --> 20:11.079
- Ah, you--Nick, you can't let
her do this! Aah!

20:11.122 --> 20:12.733
- Pull it out
your puckered blue--

20:12.776 --> 20:14.387
- Hey.
- What's the damage?

20:14.430 --> 20:16.215
- I told her we were
at Coney Island.

20:16.258 --> 20:17.694
You tried to win me
a stuffed animal,

20:17.738 --> 20:20.958
but it turns out you suck
at ring toss.

20:21.002 --> 20:24.179
- Wha--you lied for me?

20:24.223 --> 20:25.876
- Is that bad?

20:25.920 --> 20:27.226
- Well, not in this case,

20:27.269 --> 20:28.749
but if you wanted to go
to Coney Island,

20:28.792 --> 20:30.316
all you had to do was--
- I don't.

20:30.359 --> 20:33.057
[melancholy music]

20:33.101 --> 20:34.320
- What pony did you pick?

20:34.363 --> 20:36.235
- This one.

20:36.278 --> 20:38.976
- You sure?
- Positive.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.761
Happy Hour to win.

20:40.804 --> 20:42.893
- Happy Hour?

20:47.376 --> 20:49.857
- Ooh, that kind
of lunch, huh?

20:49.900 --> 20:51.250
- Mm.
She'll have one.

20:51.293 --> 20:52.990
They have red and white.

20:53.034 --> 20:55.950
- Only white before noon.

20:55.993 --> 20:58.082
If I knew we were
diningdining,

20:58.126 --> 21:00.520
I would've worn my good suit.

21:00.563 --> 21:04.350
- What would you call
that color? Is that coral?

21:04.393 --> 21:06.874
- Paprika, maybe.
I don't know

21:06.917 --> 21:09.355
- Well, here's to paprika.

21:09.398 --> 21:11.182
- Ah, paprika.
[glasses clink]

21:13.402 --> 21:16.840
So to what do I owe
the mid-morning buzz?

21:16.884 --> 21:19.321
- It's been a while.
Wanted to check in.

21:19.365 --> 21:22.803
- And everyone else you know
would judge.

21:22.846 --> 21:25.153
- Mental-health days
are a real thing.

21:25.196 --> 21:28.374
- Oh, mm-hmm.

21:28.417 --> 21:30.419
And the kid?

21:32.552 --> 21:35.119
- Thank you.
I will have another.

21:37.948 --> 21:40.342
Mmm.

21:40.386 --> 21:43.998
New private school--
8,000 per quarter.

21:44.041 --> 21:45.347
- Holy shit.

21:45.391 --> 21:48.959
- Believe it or not,
I'm counting on Nick.

21:51.135 --> 21:53.268
[both laughing]

21:53.312 --> 21:54.922
I know.

21:54.965 --> 21:56.924
But he wants to step up.
- Father of the year.

21:56.967 --> 21:58.360
- So I have to let him.

21:58.404 --> 22:01.537
Besides,
I could use the me time.

22:01.581 --> 22:05.367
Pick up a hobby,
dust off the old dating apps.

22:05.411 --> 22:08.979
- You didn't call me to talk
about boys, did you?

22:12.156 --> 22:15.203
Amanda, what's the matter?

22:15.246 --> 22:19.294
[ominous music]

22:19.338 --> 22:21.470
- Well...

22:21.514 --> 22:23.951
this has turned
into a hot little mess.

22:23.994 --> 22:25.953
That's the past,
I'm the future.

22:25.996 --> 22:27.084
[slaps hands]
Bam!

22:27.128 --> 22:31.045
♪

22:31.088 --> 22:33.526
- [groaning goofily,
chuckling]

22:33.569 --> 22:36.355
Red wine before noon,
you warned me.

22:36.398 --> 22:39.445
[chuckling]

22:39.488 --> 22:41.403
How about you?
Are you seeing anybody?

22:41.447 --> 22:43.971
- Fuck that.

22:44.014 --> 22:46.495
Amanda...

22:46.539 --> 22:49.977
what happened up there
that night?

22:50.020 --> 22:51.587
What happened in Shine Tower?

22:51.631 --> 22:53.981
♪

22:54.024 --> 22:57.941
- What if I told you
I can't remember?

22:57.985 --> 23:02.032
- I'd say
you've been though a lot.

23:02.076 --> 23:04.861
I'd say...

23:04.905 --> 23:06.863
you're in denial.

23:06.907 --> 23:08.996
- Wow.

23:09.039 --> 23:13.914
Cop, fucker of husbands
not your own,

23:13.957 --> 23:16.525
real-estate agent,
and now psychotherapist?

23:16.569 --> 23:19.441
Is there anything you can't do?

23:19.485 --> 23:21.443
- Yeah.

23:21.487 --> 23:25.273
Let go of this,
and neither can you.

23:27.493 --> 23:29.190
- Watch me.

23:29.233 --> 23:31.192
[glasses clink]

23:33.455 --> 23:36.197
[glass clinks, reverberates]

23:36.240 --> 23:37.416
- Happy Hour and
The Land of Piss and Fire

23:37.459 --> 23:39.113
are out of the gate fast,

23:39.156 --> 23:41.245
but Happy Hour takes
a commanding lead.

23:41.289 --> 23:43.552
[all shouting]
- Come on, baby!

23:43.596 --> 23:46.250
- Happy Hour has opened up
the lead by three lengths.

23:46.294 --> 23:48.514
Happy Hour
has the race sewn up.

23:48.557 --> 23:50.907
Oh, no! Happy Hour down!

23:50.951 --> 23:52.300
- Get back on the horse!

23:52.343 --> 23:53.475
- Happy Hour has broken
his leg!

23:53.519 --> 23:55.216
- Get back on the horse!

23:55.259 --> 23:56.609
- Send him to
the glue factory, folks!

23:56.652 --> 23:58.001
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
You had a good run, kid.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.133
You can't win 'em all.

23:59.176 --> 24:00.264
- Nah, nah, nah!
Yes, she can.

24:00.308 --> 24:01.701
No, no. Sit--sit down.
Sit down.

24:01.744 --> 24:04.965
Let's just pick another horse.
Pick another horse.

24:05.008 --> 24:06.401
- I'm out of money.

24:06.445 --> 24:07.533
- Well, I got to--
I'll find the fucking money!

24:07.576 --> 24:10.492
- Sax, ease up.
- Back off!

24:10.536 --> 24:12.494
- [voice breaking] It's not fun
anymore. I don't want to.

24:12.538 --> 24:14.061
- What are you talking about
it's not fun?

24:14.104 --> 24:16.542
This is fun!
Just--just pick another horse.

24:16.585 --> 24:19.066
- I don't want to!
- Just pick a stupid horse.

24:26.160 --> 24:28.684
Oh, sure. Like you guys
are all great parents.

24:28.728 --> 24:30.207
- [crying]

24:30.251 --> 24:32.558
- Oh, slow down,
little one!

24:32.601 --> 24:34.429
- Thank goodness,
a cowboy!

24:34.473 --> 24:36.126
- You should be more careful.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.172
- Hailey, you can't just run
off like that.

24:38.215 --> 24:39.956
I mean, what if your mom
had found out.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.392
- You know,
your father is right.

24:41.436 --> 24:43.264
It's important to keep
your family close.

24:43.307 --> 24:45.658
- I don't remember anyone
asking your advice, pal.

24:45.701 --> 24:48.312
- Shalom...Sax.

24:48.356 --> 24:50.967
[ominous music]

24:51.011 --> 24:53.666
Oh, please, just a...word.

24:53.709 --> 24:59.367
♪

24:59.410 --> 25:00.586
My name is David.

25:00.629 --> 25:02.544
Those were my men
that you, uh,

25:02.588 --> 25:04.503
mingled with at the party
last night.

25:04.546 --> 25:07.070
- Yeah? Well, your men
mingled with one of my friends,

25:07.114 --> 25:08.376
and they got me instead.

25:08.419 --> 25:10.291
- And that's why
I bear no ill will,

25:10.334 --> 25:13.294
yeah, but my father is
still gravely, gravely ill,

25:13.337 --> 25:15.470
and time is so precious.

25:15.514 --> 25:18.429
- Your dad's sick?
- He is, dear little one.

25:18.473 --> 25:21.128
At death's door with just
your heroic father here

25:21.171 --> 25:22.999
as his only
hope and savior.

25:23.043 --> 25:24.479
- [stammering]
That's not really true.

25:24.523 --> 25:26.089
That's--that's not true.

25:26.133 --> 25:28.483
Look, um, your men made
the first move.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.137
I just reacted.

25:30.180 --> 25:32.182
- Yeah,
what a reaction it was,

25:32.226 --> 25:34.489
and yet a deed
remains to be done.

25:34.533 --> 25:38.232
A mitzvah, if you will,
for Passover.

25:38.275 --> 25:40.147
See, we've--we've found
another match

25:40.190 --> 25:41.627
My brother Saul has
the kidney,

25:41.670 --> 25:43.585
simply pick it up,
bring it to me.

25:43.629 --> 25:45.587
- So call an errand boy.
- But you can help.

25:45.631 --> 25:47.502
- No, you don't understand,
honey.

25:47.546 --> 25:49.069
- He'll die if you don't.

25:49.112 --> 25:51.158
- Yes, that is the truth,
little one,

25:51.201 --> 25:53.726
and because the kidney will be
coming to us through, uh,

25:53.769 --> 25:55.684
well, special circumstances,

25:55.728 --> 25:58.600
it requires a special man,
like your father here,

25:58.644 --> 26:01.690
to go pick it up
and deliver.

26:01.734 --> 26:06.303
♪

26:06.347 --> 26:09.524
- Dad.

26:09.568 --> 26:12.092
- Oh, Nicholas, please,

26:12.135 --> 26:15.095
let us not allow the problems
that have transpired

26:15.138 --> 26:17.271
to lead to the death
of an innocent man.

26:17.314 --> 26:18.794
- No one is innocent.

26:18.838 --> 26:20.535
- Yes, many have fallen,

26:20.579 --> 26:24.626
but forgiveness is usually
followed by atonement.

26:24.670 --> 26:31.067
♪

26:31.111 --> 26:33.679
- Pick up?
- And delivery.

26:33.722 --> 26:35.724
♪

26:35.768 --> 26:38.727
- [clicks tongue]
Give me the address.

26:38.771 --> 26:41.208
- Here, here's Saul's house,
my number.

26:41.251 --> 26:43.732
Call when the kidney's in hand.
We'll arrange a drop.

26:43.776 --> 26:46.779
♪

26:46.822 --> 26:48.345
Shalom.

26:48.389 --> 26:53.307
♪

26:56.136 --> 26:59.008
[light music playing
over speakers]

26:59.052 --> 27:05.928
♪

27:05.972 --> 27:09.018
- Amanda?

27:09.062 --> 27:10.672
How are you?

27:10.716 --> 27:12.761
- Simon, hi.

27:12.805 --> 27:16.112
- [smooches]

27:16.156 --> 27:18.767
- I'm sorry I never called.

27:18.811 --> 27:22.684
Things got...busy
over the holidays.

27:22.728 --> 27:25.644
- I saw the posters.
Everyone okay?

27:25.687 --> 27:28.081
- We're managing.
Thank you.

27:28.124 --> 27:31.040
- Looks like, uh, somebody
caught the Easter Fever.

27:31.084 --> 27:32.651
Hmm?

27:32.694 --> 27:34.217
- Um...

27:34.261 --> 27:36.655
- I'm just teasing you. I mean,
hey, it's everywhere, right?

27:36.698 --> 27:38.831
Easter--it's like a thing
this year.

27:38.874 --> 27:40.702
- I know, right?

27:40.746 --> 27:45.272
We--we never really
celebrated it before,

27:45.315 --> 27:48.188
but I thought
my daughter might,

27:48.231 --> 27:50.190
you know,
want some holiday cheer.

27:50.233 --> 27:53.584
It's silly.
- No, it's not.

27:53.628 --> 27:55.717
Look,
I'm not a religious guy,

27:55.761 --> 27:58.241
but for me, the season
has a-a feeling

27:58.285 --> 28:00.896
of--of something new.

28:00.940 --> 28:03.203
Springtime,
New York City, huh?

28:03.246 --> 28:06.119
I mean, a resurrection, whether
you believe in that or not,

28:06.162 --> 28:08.861
it's symbolic.

28:08.904 --> 28:11.124
It's a chance to see
the world with fresh eyes.

28:12.821 --> 28:15.084
Besides, I love these things.

28:15.128 --> 28:17.913
[crinkling]

28:17.957 --> 28:21.003
- I like those, too.

28:21.047 --> 28:23.092
[crinkling]

28:23.136 --> 28:24.920
♪

28:31.927 --> 28:33.624
- I want to go in.

28:33.668 --> 28:35.235
- Nah, it'll just take me
a minute. Don't move.

28:35.278 --> 28:36.976
- You can't leave her
in the car.

28:37.019 --> 28:38.412
- You're thinking of dogs
in a heat wave.

28:38.455 --> 28:40.327
She'll be fine. You just
make sure she stays put.

28:40.370 --> 28:42.416
- So you're leaving both of us.

28:42.459 --> 28:44.157
I don't know
what sucks eggs more--

28:44.200 --> 28:46.637
your dad game
or your partner game.

28:46.681 --> 28:47.638
[doorbell rings]

28:47.682 --> 28:49.249
[spraying]

28:49.292 --> 28:51.817
- I'm looking
for Milwaukee Saul.

28:51.860 --> 28:53.949
- Papa!

28:53.993 --> 28:57.779
- No running in the house.

28:57.823 --> 28:59.302
Hi, I'm Saul.

28:59.346 --> 29:01.087
- Yeah, I'm here
for the package.

29:01.130 --> 29:04.090
- Package?
- David sent me.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.832
Come on, the meter is running.
Let's just pack it up, huh?

29:06.875 --> 29:08.442
- [panting]
I couldn't stop her, Nick!

29:08.485 --> 29:10.749
- What are you talking about?
- Who's this little one?

29:10.792 --> 29:14.274
- I'm starving, Dad.
- Hailey, go back to the cab.

29:14.317 --> 29:16.798
- Come,
Shabbos is about to start.

29:16.842 --> 29:18.669
- Is that food?
- Plenty of it.

29:18.713 --> 29:21.411
- Thank God.
- Oh, food. I'm hungry.

29:23.892 --> 29:25.328
- You had one job.

29:28.854 --> 29:30.725
One job.

29:32.858 --> 29:34.294
[silverware clattering]

29:34.337 --> 29:38.124
- You dad drives a taxi?
- He used to be a cop.

29:38.167 --> 29:40.126
- My dad owns
four jewelry stores,

29:40.169 --> 29:43.956
three tanning salons,
and two Maybachs

29:43.999 --> 29:47.089
- Well,
my dad killed Santa Claus.

29:49.875 --> 29:51.790
- We're Jewish.

29:54.270 --> 29:56.838
- She's lovely.

29:56.882 --> 29:58.013
- What's it to you?

29:58.057 --> 29:59.841
- Just a compliment.
Take it.

29:59.885 --> 30:01.843
It's not easy being a father.

30:01.887 --> 30:04.019
- Yeah, you seem
to be doing all right with it.

30:04.063 --> 30:06.413
- Yeah, only seven are mine,
one planned.

30:06.456 --> 30:08.154
And the eldest needs somebody
to play with.

30:08.197 --> 30:09.851
You know how it is.
- Look, let's take care of--

30:09.895 --> 30:12.898
- You have brothers?
- No.

30:12.941 --> 30:15.335
- One day I'm bullying David
in our parents' backyard,

30:15.378 --> 30:16.989
the next...

30:17.032 --> 30:18.947
he's squeezing me
out of the family business.

30:18.991 --> 30:20.340
- Seems like something
I don't care about.

30:20.383 --> 30:22.385
- Your reputation
precedes you, Mr. Sax.

30:22.429 --> 30:24.474
Tell me, you here today,

30:24.518 --> 30:27.521
should I take from this
you are, uh, shall we say,

30:27.564 --> 30:30.002
still employable?

30:32.178 --> 30:34.876
- I was so curious why you were
so generous with your bone.

30:34.920 --> 30:37.879
So, sadly, uh,
you're a few months too late.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.185
I don't do that no more.

30:39.228 --> 30:42.275
Now, you've been
a wonderful host.

30:42.318 --> 30:45.887
Kindly fetch that package,
and we'll be on our way.

30:45.931 --> 30:50.196
- [chuckling]
The package.

30:50.239 --> 30:52.807
- Yeah, the package.

30:52.851 --> 30:54.374
- It's right here.

30:54.417 --> 30:56.158
Come get it.

30:56.202 --> 30:59.161
[ominous music]

30:59.205 --> 31:02.034
- Are we ready
for the next one?

31:02.077 --> 31:05.385
N-37.

31:05.428 --> 31:08.910
B-5.
[telephone ringing]

31:08.954 --> 31:10.564
- Shalom.
- Up yours, Yentl.

31:10.607 --> 31:12.914
You told me the package was
a kidney, not a whole human.

31:12.958 --> 31:14.481
- Oh, it is a kidney.

31:14.524 --> 31:16.352
How you choose to deliver it,
uh, that's your prerogative.

31:16.396 --> 31:18.398
- He's not gonna just gonna
jump in my cab, now, is he?

31:18.441 --> 31:20.879
- Oh, well, then you need
to persuade him.

31:20.922 --> 31:22.358
- You want me to kill him.

31:22.402 --> 31:25.013
- Well, that's entirely up
to you, but, uh, yes.

31:25.057 --> 31:27.581
- The kid's here.
- Well, then be careful.

31:27.624 --> 31:30.062
I don't want any dead children
on my conscience.

31:30.105 --> 31:32.064
- You know, I'm getting mighty
tired of you two dickheads.

31:32.107 --> 31:34.022
I tell you what.
- I-28.

31:34.066 --> 31:36.938
- I am gonna kill your brother
and tear our his kidney,

31:36.982 --> 31:38.592
and then I'm gonna feed it
to his fucking dog

31:38.635 --> 31:40.986
and let your old man croak
in a puddle of his own piss.

31:41.029 --> 31:42.813
- Yeah, I wouldn't do that,
Sax.

31:42.857 --> 31:44.946
It'd be a shame if something
terrible were to happen

31:44.990 --> 31:46.817
to that beautiful daughter
of yours.

31:46.861 --> 31:49.081
Oh, oh, and, um, just
so we're clear this time,

31:49.124 --> 31:50.952
"something terrible"
means we kill her.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.388
- Bingo!

31:52.432 --> 31:54.390
- Another winner in the hall!
[bell dings]

31:54.434 --> 31:56.262
- Shalom.

31:56.305 --> 31:58.003
[applause]

31:58.046 --> 32:00.092
[ominous music]

32:00.135 --> 32:02.964
- [clicks tongue]

32:03.008 --> 32:04.966
[bones crack]

32:05.010 --> 32:08.839
♪

32:08.883 --> 32:11.190
Come here.

32:11.233 --> 32:14.062
I need you to go out
to the cab and stay there.

32:14.106 --> 32:16.064
Call your mom, tell her we're
going to be a little late.

32:16.108 --> 32:18.414
♪

32:18.458 --> 32:21.461
Papa's got some business
to take care of.

32:21.504 --> 32:28.511
♪

32:30.078 --> 32:32.385
[car horns honking]

32:34.039 --> 32:41.002
♪

32:42.264 --> 32:44.571
[tapping]

32:48.270 --> 32:51.230
- What are you doing
at Shine Tower, Geno?

32:53.275 --> 32:55.408
- Audition
for the fifth Wishee.

32:56.931 --> 32:59.151
[groans] You can't do that.
You ain't a cop anymore.

32:59.194 --> 33:00.935
- Says who?

33:00.979 --> 33:02.545
- You're wearing
a real-estate jacket.

33:02.589 --> 33:05.244
- I may not be a cop anymore,

33:05.287 --> 33:07.333
but I can still get away
with murder.

33:07.376 --> 33:10.423
- Oh, careful, I need those.

33:13.078 --> 33:15.645
You're Blue's
personal lawyer, Geno.

33:15.689 --> 33:18.605
I would love to know what you
and Sonny had to talk about.

33:18.648 --> 33:21.216
- You are wasting your--
[screams]

33:21.260 --> 33:24.219
[whimpering]

33:24.263 --> 33:27.005
You can't.
No one can touch to Shine.

33:27.048 --> 33:29.050
No cop. No one.

33:29.094 --> 33:31.400
- Oh?
- He's got dirt.

33:31.444 --> 33:34.055
[exhales sharply]
Blackmail on everyone.

33:34.099 --> 33:36.188
That's how he does it.

33:36.231 --> 33:41.193
- Good, tell me something
I don't know.

33:41.236 --> 33:43.195
- It's on videotape.

33:43.238 --> 33:46.024
Yeah, I know. The fucking guy
don't believe in digital.

33:46.067 --> 33:48.069
"Tape is forever," he says.

33:48.113 --> 33:49.549
[breathing heavily]

33:49.592 --> 33:51.638
He knows what people wish for--

33:51.681 --> 33:53.292
the dark stuff,

33:53.335 --> 33:56.077
the stuff they don't even tell
their shrinks about--

33:56.121 --> 33:58.427
and he gives it to them.

33:58.471 --> 34:01.126
Then he owns them.

34:01.169 --> 34:03.650
- I've done my homework on you.

34:03.693 --> 34:05.304
You've known Blue
for 20 years.

34:05.347 --> 34:07.088
He was at your wedding.

34:07.132 --> 34:08.959
He's godfather
to your first daughter,

34:09.003 --> 34:11.266
but you sold him out.

34:11.310 --> 34:13.225
Sold him out
to this cheap circus clown,

34:13.268 --> 34:17.316
this maggot, when you know
exactly what Sonny Shine does.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.187
- [shudders]
- What he does to kids--

34:19.231 --> 34:22.103
kids no older than
your own little girl.

34:22.147 --> 34:25.237
- [sniffs]
- Why?

34:25.280 --> 34:27.195
- [shudders]

34:27.239 --> 34:28.979
He's got a tape on me.

34:29.023 --> 34:32.026
[breathing heavily]

34:34.289 --> 34:36.509
- Okay.

34:36.552 --> 34:39.468
Then you got something to lose,

34:39.512 --> 34:41.644
but I don't.

34:41.688 --> 34:44.082
Tell me where he keeps
the tapes.

34:50.175 --> 34:54.004
- [grunts] Care to share
what's in the notebook?

34:54.048 --> 34:57.138
- Care to share
what's in the ice bucket?

35:02.274 --> 35:04.450
Didn't think so.

35:13.285 --> 35:16.549
- All right.
- I know, stay in the car.

35:16.592 --> 35:18.333
- Yeah.

35:18.377 --> 35:22.250
[dramatic music]

35:22.294 --> 35:25.471
- Oh, Mr. Sax!

35:25.514 --> 35:27.647
[feedback whines]
What a pleasant surprise.

35:27.690 --> 35:29.170
I got to be honest, I, uh--

35:29.214 --> 35:30.650
I wasn't sure
that you'd come through,

35:30.693 --> 35:32.652
but, boy,
I'm so glad that you did.

35:32.695 --> 35:34.262
- Me too.
- Gentlemen?

35:34.306 --> 35:36.699
- You know, I--
Call me narrow-minded,

35:36.743 --> 35:39.180
but I didn't have you pegged
as a bingo nut.

35:39.224 --> 35:40.660
- I know, I know.

35:40.703 --> 35:42.357
We collected this property
to settle a debt,

35:42.401 --> 35:45.099
but who knew that it would be
such a gold mine?

35:45.143 --> 35:47.493
The senior population is
just exploding.

35:47.536 --> 35:49.234
Bingo!
[chuckling]

35:49.277 --> 35:50.409
It's the future.

35:50.452 --> 35:51.758
- Well, you know,
me personally,

35:51.801 --> 35:53.629
I don't put much stock
in the future.

35:55.631 --> 35:57.242
So, if we're done chitchatting,

35:57.285 --> 35:58.852
why don't we just take care
of you and your mitzvah?

35:58.895 --> 36:01.246
- Oh, yeah, by all means.

36:01.289 --> 36:04.814
- [inhales deeply]
[locks click]

36:09.384 --> 36:12.344
[rock music]

36:12.387 --> 36:18.393
♪

36:18.437 --> 36:21.396
[gun clicking]

36:21.440 --> 36:25.748
♪

36:25.792 --> 36:28.142
[blows landing]

36:28.186 --> 36:32.451
♪

36:32.494 --> 36:34.148
[gunshot]

36:34.192 --> 36:36.890
♪

36:36.933 --> 36:38.892
[man groaning]

36:38.935 --> 36:41.808
[crashing]

36:41.851 --> 36:45.159
[blows landing]

36:45.203 --> 36:46.378
[clattering]

36:46.421 --> 36:47.727
- [yelling]

36:47.770 --> 36:50.295
[crashing]

36:50.338 --> 36:53.863
[groaning, wheezing]

36:53.907 --> 36:55.865
- Don't ever fuck
with my family.

36:55.909 --> 36:58.259
- [lisping]
Please...

36:58.303 --> 36:59.869
it's Passover.

36:59.913 --> 37:01.393
[wheezes]

37:01.436 --> 37:02.742
Mitzvah.

37:02.785 --> 37:04.134
[wheezes]

37:04.178 --> 37:05.397
- Eat shitz-vah.

37:05.440 --> 37:07.703
[gunshot, bell dinging]

37:10.663 --> 37:13.231
- We heard it, Nick.
All of it!

37:14.623 --> 37:17.626
- Oh, boy, those guys
and their fireworks.

37:17.670 --> 37:20.673
[breathing heavily] I mean,
who knew it was a Jewish thing?

37:22.457 --> 37:23.676
Are you okay?

37:23.719 --> 37:24.938
- Yeah, you?

37:24.981 --> 37:26.418
- Good. Great.

37:26.461 --> 37:28.768
You know, anytime I get
to spend

37:28.811 --> 37:30.813
a day with my little cupcake,
I mean...

37:30.857 --> 37:32.946
[breathing heavily]
I call that a lucky day.

37:32.989 --> 37:35.296
I call that, uh...

37:35.340 --> 37:36.950
the best day
a dad could ever have.

37:36.993 --> 37:39.169
- Did you kill those people?

37:39.213 --> 37:42.216
[ominous music]

37:42.260 --> 37:46.873
♪

37:46.916 --> 37:48.875
- I dropped off a package.
That's all.

37:48.918 --> 37:51.443
- Just tell me the truth.

37:51.486 --> 37:54.315
He set you up,
so you killed them.

37:54.359 --> 37:56.317
- Hailey,
there are certain things

37:56.361 --> 37:57.623
that you just can't know.

37:57.666 --> 37:58.841
- I already do.

37:58.885 --> 38:00.843
- And you got to forget it...

38:00.887 --> 38:02.889
[siren wailing in the distance]

38:02.932 --> 38:04.891
Now and forever.

38:04.934 --> 38:07.894
[siren continues wailing]

38:07.937 --> 38:09.417
It's for your own good.

38:09.461 --> 38:11.811
- I thought we could be real
with each other,

38:11.854 --> 38:14.335
but I guess I just get
Fake Dad, right?

38:14.379 --> 38:16.685
- Yeah, I guess so! I guess
teddy bears and Coney Island

38:16.729 --> 38:18.513
are gonna have
to be good enough

38:18.557 --> 38:20.385
like they are
for every other kid.

38:20.428 --> 38:24.302
- I really wish things were
the way they used to be.

38:32.614 --> 38:34.616
- You mean before me?

38:36.270 --> 38:38.272
- [sighs]

38:42.798 --> 38:45.932
- She really didn't mean that.

38:48.543 --> 38:49.979
- Blow me.

38:50.023 --> 38:53.983
- [exhaling deeply]

38:54.027 --> 38:56.246
Like that?

38:59.685 --> 39:02.122
[clicking]

39:02.165 --> 39:05.125
[Jimmy Wakely's
"Peter Cottontail" plays]

39:05.168 --> 39:06.866
♪

39:06.909 --> 39:08.389
[hissing]

39:08.433 --> 39:10.435
- ♪ Here comes
Peter Cottontail ♪

39:10.478 --> 39:12.393
♪ Hopping down
the bunny trail ♪

39:12.437 --> 39:17.180
♪ Hippity hoppin',
Easter's on its way ♪

39:17.224 --> 39:19.705
♪ Bringing every girl
and boy ♪

39:19.748 --> 39:22.098
♪ Baskets full
of Easter joy ♪

39:22.142 --> 39:25.928
♪ Things to make your Easter
bright and gay ♪

39:25.972 --> 39:27.452
[rabbit squeaks]

39:27.495 --> 39:29.367
♪ He's got jelly beans
for Tommy ♪

39:29.410 --> 39:32.065
♪ Colored eggs
for sister Sue ♪

39:34.502 --> 39:36.069
- Good night, Hailey.

39:37.853 --> 39:39.855
[high-pitched voice]
"Good night, Dad."

39:41.770 --> 39:43.424
[normal voice]
Wow.

39:43.468 --> 39:44.991
- Oh, evening.

39:45.034 --> 39:47.167
Aah!

39:47.210 --> 39:48.908
What the hell?

39:48.951 --> 39:50.388
You must be Nick.

39:50.431 --> 39:52.433
Amanda's t-told me
so much about you.

39:52.477 --> 39:53.826
- Who the fuck are you?

39:53.869 --> 39:55.088
- I--
- Nick, is that you?

39:55.131 --> 39:56.872
- Oh, yeah.
- Oh.

39:56.916 --> 39:58.352
Good. You two met.

39:58.396 --> 40:01.877
- Simon.

40:01.921 --> 40:04.227
I heard Hailey got to spend
a day with Dad.

40:04.271 --> 40:06.012
Good times.

40:06.055 --> 40:09.232
We were just putting up
some Easter decorations.

40:09.276 --> 40:10.364
- Were we?

40:10.408 --> 40:11.757
- Don't be rude, Nick.

40:11.800 --> 40:13.802
- You...

40:16.414 --> 40:17.371
Work together?

40:17.415 --> 40:20.200
- Huh? Oh, no, no, no.

40:20.243 --> 40:23.856
I, uh--I did consider studying
medicine for a hot minute

40:23.899 --> 40:25.379
when, uh--
when I was in college,

40:25.423 --> 40:29.252
but in the end, I decided
to become an entrepreneur.

40:29.296 --> 40:30.819
Neck ties.

40:30.863 --> 40:33.735
- Neck ties?
- Yeah, with a twist.

40:33.779 --> 40:35.868
- Bow ties?

40:35.911 --> 40:37.347
- [laughing] Bow ties?

40:37.391 --> 40:40.916
[both laughing]

40:40.960 --> 40:44.180
- No, you see, I-I believe it's
important to--to give back.

40:44.224 --> 40:46.052
So, for every tie that we sell,

40:46.095 --> 40:49.055
we donate one to an indigenous
person from the third world.

40:49.098 --> 40:50.883
Yeah, it helps to create
a feeling of self-esteem,

40:50.926 --> 40:53.015
as well as prepare them
for possible job interviews.

40:53.059 --> 40:54.887
- Fascinating.
- Thanks.

40:54.930 --> 40:56.236
- Sorry about the--
- Oh, no, hey.

40:56.279 --> 40:57.498
Absolutely no worries,
big guy.

40:57.542 --> 40:59.239
Look, a stranger
in your ex-wife's house?

40:59.282 --> 41:00.849
With everything
that happened recently?

41:00.893 --> 41:03.156
I get it. Totally.

41:05.332 --> 41:08.030
Anyway, I should be going.

41:08.074 --> 41:11.817
Oh, my God.
That stuff gets everywhere.

41:13.514 --> 41:17.344
[both chuckling]

41:17.387 --> 41:19.085
Nice to meet you, Nick.

41:19.128 --> 41:21.130
I'll call you later.

41:25.134 --> 41:27.485
- He's just a friend.
- An Easter friend.

41:27.528 --> 41:29.487
- Mm.

41:31.184 --> 41:32.141
What's up with Hailey?

41:32.185 --> 41:33.447
- Ah?

41:33.491 --> 41:34.535
- Stormed upstairs
without a word?

41:34.579 --> 41:37.233
- Uh, I...

41:38.931 --> 41:42.369
- Been thinking
about that tuition?

41:42.412 --> 41:44.153
- Now that you mention it,

41:44.197 --> 41:47.200
I got offered a stack of cash
today for a quick job.

41:49.419 --> 41:53.162
I turned it down.
Just wanted you to know that.

41:55.295 --> 41:57.166
- Don't worry, Nick.

41:57.210 --> 42:00.039
[inhales deeply]
It's all gonna work out.

42:00.082 --> 42:02.302
[dramatic music]

42:02.345 --> 42:04.957
Mm!

42:05.000 --> 42:11.877
♪

42:11.920 --> 42:15.010
- Boy, Amanda's in
a really good mood.

42:17.360 --> 42:19.362
- She just fucked that guy.

42:28.067 --> 42:29.851
[plop]

42:29.895 --> 42:32.985
- ♪ Little doggies

42:33.028 --> 42:36.162
♪ It's your misfortune

42:36.205 --> 42:38.251
♪ None of my own

42:57.226 --> 43:01.013
You tell Sonny Shine...

43:01.056 --> 43:02.188
[clicks tongue]

43:02.231 --> 43:04.538
Vaffanculo.

43:04.582 --> 43:07.933
[suspenseful music]

43:07.976 --> 43:14.983
♪

43:25.298 --> 43:28.257
[choking]

43:28.301 --> 43:34.133
♪

43:35.656 --> 43:40.530
- Today was pretty much
the best day ever.

43:40.574 --> 43:43.403
I got to hang out
with my dad.

43:43.446 --> 43:47.102
First, he made me
a big breakfast.

43:49.061 --> 43:50.410
We saw some ponies.

43:50.453 --> 43:51.629
- I'm out of money.
- Well, I got to--

43:51.672 --> 43:53.456
I'll find the fucking money!

43:53.500 --> 43:57.069
- He introduced me to new
and interesting people.

43:57.112 --> 43:58.679
- Hey, Saxy.

43:58.723 --> 44:01.595
- And exposed me to other
cultures and religions.

44:01.639 --> 44:03.466
[explosion]

44:03.510 --> 44:05.991
We really got to know a lot
more about each other,

44:06.034 --> 44:08.602
which is important
for a father and daughter--

44:08.646 --> 44:12.693
to be close,
to trust one another.

44:12.737 --> 44:16.523
After all, if you can't
trust your parents,

44:16.566 --> 44:18.699
who can you trust?

44:18.743 --> 44:21.702
[solemn music]

44:21.746 --> 44:28.709
♪

44:28.753 --> 44:31.712
[Jimmy Wakely's
"Peter Cottontail"]

44:31.756 --> 44:37.500
♪

44:37.544 --> 44:39.241
[rabbit squealing]

44:39.285 --> 44:41.330
- ♪ Here comes
Peter Cottontail ♪

44:41.374 --> 44:44.159
♪ Hopping down
the bunny trail ♪

44:44.203 --> 44:48.990
♪ Look at him stop
and listen to him say ♪

